 examples to impart fundamental knowledge about the application of market research instruments in actual library practice. The focus is on applying methods and scenarios that are targeted at optimizing or expanding user-related services. The range of applications includes customer satisfaction surveys and questionnaire-based inquiries about the information behavior of library users, and a discussion of “mystery shopping” as a building block for systematic quality management. In addition, it discusses usability testing for library websites and the use of online research tools (e.g. catalogues, local portals).  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aInformation behaviorxResearch. 0aLibrariesxEvaluation. 0aLibrary Web sitesxTesting. 0aLibrary usersxAttitudes. 0aOnline information servicesxUse studies. 0aPublic services (Libraries)xEvaluation. 4aBibliothek. 4aMarktforschung. 4aQualitätsmanagement. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh  aMarket research.  alibraries.  aquality management.1 aNix, Sebastian Johannes, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Library Information Science 2000 - 2014z9783110636246oZDB-23-GLI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET BIBLIOTHEKSWESEN, INFO UND DOKUMENTATION 2013z9783110317213oZDB-23-DGB0 cprintz978311027623740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311027630540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110276305423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110276305/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aP